<refnamediv>
<refname>npm-help-search</refname>
<refpurpose>Search npm help documentation</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
<para>npm help-search &lt;text&gt;</para>
</refsynopsisdiv>


<refsect1 id='description'><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<para>This command will search the npm markdown documentation files for the
terms provided, and then list the results, sorted by relevance.</para>

<para>If only one result is found, then it will show that help topic.</para>

<para>If the argument to <emphasis remap='B'>npm help</emphasis> is not a known help topic, then it will
call <emphasis remap='B'>help-search</emphasis>&thinsp;.  It is rarely if ever necessary to call this
command directly.</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id='configuration'><title>CONFIGURATION</title>

<refsect2 id='long'><title>long</title>
  <blockquote remap='RS'>
  <itemizedlist remap='IP+bullet'>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Type: Boolean</para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem override='bullet'>
<para>Default false</para>

    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  </blockquote> <!-- remap='RE' -->

<para>If true, the "long" flag will cause help-search to output context around
where the terms were found in the documentation.</para>

<para>If false, then help-search will just list out the help topics found.</para>
</refsect2>
</refsect1>

